    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\" />\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\" />\n<title>Hash Functions Demo</title>\n<style>\n  body {\n    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n    margin: 2rem auto;\n    max-width: 600px;\n    padding: 0 1rem;\n    background: #f5f5f5;\n    color: #333;\n  }\n  h1 {\n    text-align: center;\n    color: #005a9c;\n  }\n  label {\n    font-weight: bold;\n    display: block;\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n  }\n  input[type=\"text\"] {\n    width: 100%;\n    padding: 0.5rem;\n    font-size: 1rem;\n    margin-top: 0.25rem;\n    box-sizing: border-box;\n  }\n  button {\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n    padding: 0.7rem 1.2rem;\n    font-size: 1rem;\n    border: none;\n    background-color: #005a9c;\n    color: white;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    cursor: pointer;\n  }\n  button:hover {\n    background-color: #003f6b;\n  }\n  .hash-output {\n    margin-top: 1rem;\n    background: white;\n    padding: 1rem;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-family: monospace;\n    word-break: break-all;\n    box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);\n  }\n  .explanation {\n    margin-top: 2rem;\n    background: #e8f0fe;\n    padding: 1rem;\n    border-left: 5px solid #005a9c;\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  .note {\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    color: #555;\n    margin-top: 0.5rem;\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h1>Hash Functions Demonstration</h1>\n\n<label for=\"inputText\">Enter text to hash:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"inputText\" placeholder=\"Type something...\" />\n\n<button id=\"hashBtn\">Generate Hash (SHA-256)</button>\n\n<div id=\"output\" class=\"hash-output\" aria-live=\"polite\"></div>\n\n<div class=\"explanation\">\n  <h2>What is a Hash Function?</h2>\n  <p>A <strong>hash function</strong> takes input data (of any size) and produces a fixed-size string of characters, which appears random. Even a small change in the input produces a drastically different output. Hashes are commonly used for data integrity, digital signatures, and storing passwords securely.</p>\n  <p><strong>Properties of cryptographic hash functions include:</strong></p>\n  <ul>\n    <li><strong>Deterministic:</strong> Same input always produces the same hash.</li>\n    <li><strong>Fast Computation:</strong> The hash can be calculated quickly.</li>\n    <li><strong>Pre-image Resistance:</strong> Given a hash, it should be computationally infeasible to find the original input.</li>\n    <li><strong>Collision Resistance:</strong> It should be difficult to find two different inputs with the same hash.</li>\n    <li><strong>Avalanche Effect:</strong> Small input changes produce drastically different hashes.</li>\n  </ul>\n  <p>In this demo, we use SHA-256, a widely used cryptographic hash function that produces a 256-bit (32-byte) hash value.</p>\n</div>\n\n<script>\n// Utility: Converts ArrayBuffer to hex string\nfunction bufferToHex(buffer) {\n  return [...new Uint8Array(buffer)]\n    .map(b => b.toString(16).padStart(2, '0'))\n    .join('');\n}\n\nasync function generateHash(text) {\n  // encode as UTF-8\n  const encoder = new TextEncoder();\n  const data = encoder.encode(text);\n  // digest returns a Promise of ArrayBuffer\n  const hashBuffer = await crypto.subtle.digest('SHA-256', data);\n  return bufferToHex(hashBuffer);\n}\n\n// Event listeners\nconst input = document.getElementById('inputText');\nconst button = document.getElementById('hashBtn');\nconst output = document.getElementById('output');\n\nbutton.addEventListener('click', async () => {\n  const text = input.value.trim();\n  if (!text) {\n    output.textContent = 'Please enter some text to hash.';\n    return;\n  }\n  output.textContent = 'Calculating hash...';\n  try {\n    const hash = await generateHash(text);\n    output.innerHTML = `<strong>SHA-256 hash:</strong><br>${hash}`;\n  } catch (e) {\n    output.textContent = 'Error generating hash: ' + e.message;\n  }\n});\n\n// Optional: Update hash live as user types (uncomment to enable)\n/*\ninput.addEventListener('input', async () => {\n  const text = input.value.trim();\n  if (!text) {\n    output.textContent = '';\n    return;\n  }\n  output.textContent = 'Calculating hash...';\n  try {\n    const hash = await generateHash(text);\n    output.innerHTML = `<strong>SHA-256 hash:</strong><br>${hash}`;\n  } catch (e) {\n    output.textContent = 'Error generating hash: ' + e.message;\n  }\n});\n*/\n</script>\n\n</body>\n</html>"
